around six months of age and the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disease" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disease" target="_blank">disease</a> usually results in death by the age of twoThe <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disease" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disease" target="_blank">disease</a> is caused by a mutation of a gene inherited from both parents but Krabbe disease only arises when both parents pass on a faulty GALC geneThere's no cure for the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disease" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disease" target="_blank">disease</a> and treatment focuses on supportive care
